caption: Super nice people and great food!
The food is excellent 😋 Tasty and portions are great
Potentially the best Indo-Pak restaurent in Chicagoland.

Nice place to have Indian Pakistani food. They have a new location now in River North Gold Coast area.  I have dined in earlier at the Lincoln Park location earlier a couple of times. This time I ordered online Chicken Biryani and Lamb Curry. Both were good. The pieces in Biryani were a little chewy but taste was good.  I would recommend their Lamb Biryani over Chicken Biryani.

Don't order via Google business which is linked to postmates and they never deliver my order, just lost $30 due to postmates. I hope that's not the case with everyone. And Food is good at Tandoor Char House
Ordered delivery over the weekend. Food was absolutely amazing. I was surprised how well it traveled, particularly in super cold weather! The butter chicken was amazing, the samosa were gigantic!
Lack of distinct taste as fusion food, nor has it the flavor of either Indian or Pakistani food that it originated from.

Amazing food. Although, I can't expand on how this compares against other local Indian restaurants, I do know this food was large in portions and delicious. The chef does a great job accommodating the spicy level you can handle.
Absolutely delicious!! Definitely recommend
Nice place to meet and catch up with family. I will probably become a regular. The bill was appropriate.

I love Pakistani food, but I also try to live a more sustainable and slightly healthier lifestyle than Pakistani takeout usually allows. Tandoor has the Pakistani flavor I look for with expanded options for people like me. Instead of the usual grilled meats, I was able to get tandoori fish, and substituted chicken biryani with shrimp biryani. Both were delicious and didn’t have the crazy amount of oil Pakistani and Indian restaurants usually have. The naan was also nice and chewy, similar to what I’ve had back home. I thoroughly enjoyed the experience!

I will start by saying the food was delicious. However... We ordered chicken saag and shrimp tikka masala. The dishes could better be named saag-saag-saag-saag with 4 small pieces of chicken, and tikka masala-tikka masala-tikka masala-tikka masala and 6 medium shrimp. We had to actively try to find the meat in the bowls. If you're looking for protein in your curry, you probably should give Tandoor Char House a pass. Maybe it was just a bad night...not sure, but I will not be returning or ordering again.
Good food, not in veryyyyy great. Worth trying once and then check out others

Ordered through Tock for pickup. Everything was ready on time and packaged perfectly for the ride home.  Samosas were amazing, Naan basket? unreal...so good , & all of the chutneys rocked my world.  Thank you, Tandoor!

This will be the last time I order from here. It used to be good but this is the second time I've ordered the chicken tikka masala and it had no flavor. It was like tomato sauce...I had to add my own garam masala to it to add some flavor.

I have ordered here a couple of times and loved the food. Food tastes like freshly made and always delivered warm. My favorite place for Indian food. Samosas with tamarind chutney and butter chicken are my favorites.

Food was absolutely fantastic. Every dish was extremely flavorful, and the spice level was perfect! The staff was extremely polite and friendly, and the service was perfect. Thank you for a wonderful meal Tandoor Char House!!  COVID EDIT: This place still does everything right. Run by two brothers who are genuinely nice people that care about their customers. We’ve ordered several times during the pandemic, and they’ve delivered perfect food every time. Thanks guys!!!

This review is long overdue. Simply put: the biriyani is EXCELLENT. Best I’ve tried, personally.  My story about the first time coming here back in May 2020: When I called in with my American AF accent, the guy verified with me I was calling the right place - I was. Not sure if that means most of their customers speak their language, but only means that YOU should go there now! He was super cool and accommodated my request to split a single meal into 2 takeout containers.  After arriving and being told my food was still being made fresh (woo), he handed me my bag, genuinely thanked me for supporting the business during the pandemic, and let me know they kindly gave me almost 2 full servings of biriyani due to my request. I was delighted, and even more so after trying it! It was amazing. Can’t wait to go back. These guys have delicious food, and are super cool/nice.

Ordered (delivery- lunch break, 6 miles away) the Chana Masala with vegetable samosa and basmati rice. It really was having a conversation in my mouth. Had to shut up and listen 🤤 not the mention it arrived hot and perfectly stacked in the bag 🤩 very good service.
Best Indian food I’ve tried !
Small place, but the food was delicious! The staff takes care of you and precautions are taken with COVID. Would definitely recommend.
entered near ten, it was not crowded. had a friend come into town and asked me to take him here again. bring your appetite because portions are generous.

I have ordered from Tandoor Char house many times. Tonight I ordered and was dissatisfied with my meal. I sent an email to the restaurant letting them know about the issues and I was contacted shortly after with an apology and an offer to refund my order. I seek out restaurants that have their own delivery so I can support them instead of Uber and Grubhub.  Tandoor has good food, fast delivery and excellent customer service.
Excellent! Everything we ordered - mixed grill, butter chicken, chicken saag, samosas, naan - was delicious. We will definitely order again.
The steaks were on point but the tandoori platter left a lot to be desired of. The chicken empanadas were superb along with the assorted Naan basket and Perfect Lassis
This place is absolutely one of my favorites. The staff was helpful and kind. Like a restaurant in Washington I liked.
Hats off to Mango Cheesecake and Tamarind Wings.
I love snacking here. Definitely worth going back to.

Very rude customer service... I do Postmates and when I went to pick up a order it stated on the app that waiting the vehicle they're not allowing anyone inside they're only doing curbside check me in and I'll bring it out to the car for you I waited outside for almost 20 minutes so I finally get tired of waiting and I called and I asked the guy I'm like you know I'm outside I'm picking up an order for XYZ and you all are bringing it out right he's a no ma'am we don't do that I'm like so you all don't do curbside because on the app and in mid-sentence the guy cuts me off and says the restaurant is open ma'am we don't do that you can come in and get it..... I'm just like I find that so rude and disrespectful it's a way to say anything and I feel like for you to be answering the phone and dealing with customers you should have a better persona and face for the restaurant

Ordered take out for the first time today. We tried the masala ceviche, tandoori mix grill, Cajun chicken boti, chicken tikka masala and lamb karahi. The food was flavorful and fresh. They stand true to their name and their tandoori items were by far the highlight of our dinner. The service was courteous and professional. I would recommend this place to others.

Perfect experience from start to finish. The gentleman taking our order was so kind it's rare to experience such wonderful customer service now a days. The food was out of this world. We usually compare food to what we've had in India, and thus far this is the closest yet. The meat samosa was so flavorful and fried to perfection. The tandoor mix included very juicy chicken and perfectly flavored moist kabob. The garlic naan was large and so fresh. Way better than the average place. We also tried the lamb, chicken, and shrimp tacos. Wow! Who knew tortilla tasted so good with Tikka masala (which also was so satisfying). For the first time I had a mango lassi where you appreciate the yogurt as well as mango fruit pieces. And to top it off, the mango cheesecake is so decadent and you can appreciate it is home made. Thank you Tandoor Char House for treating us like family and feeding us food so good we forgot we're not in India!!

You MUST try the chicken tikka masala ! hands down one of my favorite dishes in the entire city! The portions are amazing and the quality of the food is beyond 5 stars.  The staff is amazing and the new patio arrangement  is perfect !
The ambience is good, it's a nice and cozy place. The food is fine and bit pricey.

Even though the restaurant is relatively small, and it usually requires reservation in advance to avoid long wait, the food is legitimately authentic and thus worth the wait. Many Indian people that I know have confirmed that this is one of their favorite typical North Indian cuisine in Chicago. Most of the dishes in the Indian restaurants are rotated around the three main types of meat: chicken, lamb, and goat. The complimentary basket of some kind of Indian bread served with three types of dipping sauce were exceptionally outstanding. The lamb biriyani with well-seasoned, tender lamb meat cooked in the basmati rice to perfection was juiciness and flavorful, even though the kick from the heat was not for everyone to handle. Service is considerably attentive and of a high-end type. Ambiance is laid-back with dimmed lighting.

Good food and very nice staff for a telephone order and pick up. The chutneys are wonderful and fresh and unlike many curry houses they are more generous in the carry out portions. The papadums were fresh and crispy and the vegetarian dishes are excellent. Tikka masala sauce is a tad thick but  overall char house is authentic and very well priced.
I tried this place before with a friend and I am hooked since then. I loved the awesome vibes and delightful food and beverages. Keep it up.
This spot sure knows how to satisfy their customers. Consistently with a nice attitude. The food is fairly priced, always fresh and clean.

Amazing Indian food! I ordered butter chicken and garlic naan. Chicken was perfectly cooked, flavors were great. Garlic naan was fresh and light. My order was placed through DoorDash, and was stolen by another driver. The owner immediately fixed the issue without me asking, and made me another order. His courtesy was most appreciated. Plan to eat her again, I recommend you to do the same!
Delicious Indian food. BYOB - bring your own booze - @ChicagoBYOB
The food here is amazing! I love the chaat fries and chicken tikka masala. The service is always wonderful, and the owners are always there and always very friendly.
Owner was incredibly nice. Ordered from here tonight. :)
Best Tandoori Salad in the world! Owner and staff are great!
AMAZING FLAVORS!!! A must try delivery place for delicious Indian food. Love love love 💜👌
5/26/20. Take out. Food was delicious and plentiful.  We really enjoyed the lamb saag.  Not a Consistent quolity of food. The take out business significantly impacts on in house experience.

Love this place! Best Indian food I could find in Chicago. Their location is pretty small (post-COVID) if you're looking for a place to eat I would call ahead to see if they have a table available for you!

The best among all the foods was at best average. Pakros were awful. The chicken curry was blant. Never ever order biriyani if you have eaten in a good place. I had much better experience with Mild 2 spicy or Rangoli which are close by too.
Our delivery was absolutely fantastic. We will be ordering again!
This place obviously knows how to satisfy their clients. Always with a helpful attitude. The food is fairly priced, always yummy and neat.

Service and food was awesome!! I was really impressed with the place. My son ordered a chicken warp. That thing was HUGE and came with a big portion of of curly seasoned fries. It truly was enough for 2 people. I ordered 2 veg samosa and tandoor chicken. It was delicious!!! We will be returning, soon!!
Amazing restaurant. The taste of the food was very good. It’s above average breakfast food with good service and good price. Worth the visit.

Tonight was the second time coming here for dinner and once again the food was out of this world. The best Indian cuisine I’ve had in Chicago! The fusion section of the menu is not to be overlooked - especially the tikka masala tacos. The classic and star of the menu is the chicken boti, so simple and so delicious!! Don’t let the empty dining space fool you, they are running out to-go orders like there’s no tomorrow. And since they aren’t as busy in the restaurant you receive excellent service every time!
Restaurant
I went there without a reservation and the host told me I have to wait 2 hours to be seated . But they have about 5 tables empty or more and I was by myself ,REALLY!!!!

Amazing experience! Staff is spectacular food is superior! Family recipes that are to die for! I would highly suggest this restaurant not just for the food but the environment and ambiance! This is a must do experience in Chicago! Thank you for the amazing Valentine's Day experience Tandoor!
Great food great atmosphere reasonably priced
Delicious food, generous portions, warm staff and very reasonable prices. Great byob date night, and my favorite place to bring my parents when they visit town. Highly recommend.
Had a wonderful and relaxing first experience today with Boonies and Yuma. Tandoori Char House was very nice and polite as well!
This place never fails to impress. They have fresh food for reasonable prices, there are no long waits even when the place is packed.
Delicious food and great delivery. Also the service over the phone was really nice.
Food is always good, staff is helpful and friendly. Definitely recommend!
This place is amazing!  Faraz the owner is just the right guy to represent the place. Service above and beyond. They knocked it out of the park!!
My favorite Indian restaurant in Chicago! Go for the Chaat fries! Heaven!

The food was decent, but what impressed us the most was that out server went above and beyond to take care of us. Everytime we wanted some lemon, or extra raita or whatever, he was immediately on it. Will visit if Im in the area again!
Good place
Absolutely delicious

Whenever we visit Chicago, This is our favorite Indian food restaurant. The place is small ,simple and the food is fantastic,  The space is warm, authentic and the food is amazingly delicious full of the awesome flavours . They keep serving this incredible dishes that you can never go wrong with . The service is always very courteous and attentive and the staff is easy going and very friendly. Thanks!
Service and food is excellent, we’ll definitely visit again when in the city.
Awesome Biryani!
Excellent indian food. Takeout portions are large. Very generous. Highly recommend
Awesome food and great service

They food and service were great. There was, however, a pungent odor coming from the downstairs bathrooms. I'm glad that I stayed, but I probably would have been driven away by that smell had I not been meeting people
So good. Eat in because I feel like you get large portions when you're there!

Excellent, family cooked food. Very nice staff. Best Indian restaurant I’ve been to.
It’s so Pricey for nothing.!
I always come by grabbing some food in here. I loved the swift service and well prepared dishes. 5 stars from me.
It’s quite busy but need to make reservation before arrival. Food quality and taste is awesome. Service is very nice. Staff is very friendly.

We are new to town and we’re optimistic this would be our local go to. The samosas were solid but unfortunately everything else was disappointing. The naan was bland, the rice was terribly undercooked and our entrees were simply bad. The service was perfectly fine and the ambiance was underwhelming but the food itself should be the review here and it was a major bummer.
Service was great, but vegetarian food was not that good.
Amazing food with great prices - will definitely return!

Amazing food and service!  We were originally going to get delivery but I’m glad we went to the actual place because it was such a good experience. We got the chaat fries, mutter paneer tikka masala, and chicken biryani to share and they were all amazing. The chaat fries were perfectly crisp and curly, the curry had a really good, smooth flavor (with unlimited rice!), and the biryani was a HUGE pile of rice with amazing spices layered in - biryani was definitely big enough for two people to share as one dish.  Our servers were also so great - they were always coming to check in on us and were super friendly and generous. Really great, cozy atmosphere!  And the mango cheesecake definitely is reason enough to stop by - super fluffy, light, perfect balance of sweet and tart. One of our servers (who I think may be the owner?) said he developed the recipe with one of the chefs and it’s made in house.

Food was fresh and the quality was all there in each dish. The atmosphere was cozy and welcoming. Definitely going back and also it’s BYOB so you can have a really good time and enjoy some really good food. 10/10 will be recommending this place to friends.
Small area but the food is excellent. The owner is Pakistani. They have prayer mat downstairs where you can pray. The food is halal here.
Great food and great service. Owners really care about quality. Wide variety of halal cuisines. One of the better Indian restaurants in the city.
Very small portions, at their price point. We'd also asked for our food to be spicy, and it was rather bland (not even mild). It also took about an hour for the food to arrive after we ordered it.
Consistent Long wait, they consistently underestimate the prep time so you won't leave. They should be more realistic on how long the meals will take.
Steak was good. And tandoor too
Solid food often.
Decent food.
The highlight of dinner for me was the customer service. Faraz was so, so nice! We ordered the chicken Tikka masala and lamb boti, which were pretty good. The naan was amazing however!
Very fire food I go here when I have the munchies and it’s always satisfying .

Excellent dinner. Probably the best indian food I have had, but my experience is limited to Chicago and the northwest suburbs. My daughter says she's had better but that was in London UK. Tandoor chicken which I usually avoid in other indian restaurants because they tend to be dry were supremely tender and flavorful here. Also had tikka masala, biryani and a couple of other things,  and they were all good.

Food is always great!  Their fusion menu is on point.  My favorite is the ribeye steak.  I also like the burger which had this sauce on it.  Kind of tasted like butter chicken/tandoori sauce.  Some good stuff!  Oh yeah, can’t forget about the delicious chat fries!  Everything is so good.  It’s like the food goes in my stomach and is greeted by my stomach acids with the highest of honor than most foods that enter it.  This food has a special place in my stomach that only very few foods have.  Thank you char house for the amazing food!!!
Amazing spot, even better food
First time trying real Indian food.  It was so so good.  Service was very nice.  The naan bread was amazing.  We will be back... a lot!
One of the best resturant for indo-pak food. Chicken kabob and garlic naan is outstanding. Achar is so unique. Should  try this place at least once.
Great food and even better customer service.

Love the chicken biryani and a friend has tried and recommended the lamb biryani as well! However, had a bad experience with the paneer wrap! The wrap had no proper filling or sauces. It’s wrap was nothing but a thick naan with no taste. If the wrap wasn’t a disaster I would have given all 5 stars
Good service amazing food
Excellent steaks

One of the best Indian restaurants in the town. Loved our visit. Food is really nice. Biryani is good too but appetizers are those which stole the show. Loved them. Service is good and very nice. Parking is available along the street.

I’ve ordered food from here before and it’s usually good, but yesterday was just awful and won’t be ordering again. They incorrectly gave cheese naan when I asked for garlic naan. I don’t think the bread was properly made, it was very doughy in some parts. The samosas they gave me tasted off after eating one bite. I smelled them and they had this very disgusting smell coming from it. I don’t know if they gave me old samosas, if the material was expired but I couldn’t eat that either. I had ordered a chicken karhai as well, something I hadn’t tried before which turned out to be the best part. This was extremely disappointing and I will definitely not be ordering from here again.
Very original flavours and truly Indian cuisine! You just can’t skip this place.
Excellent indian cuisine
Awesome food.... The tamarind chicken wings is a must have !!

We went to Burger Fest today and we had the Tandoor Chicken Sandwich and the Tandoor Char Burger. The burger and the sauce were not a good combination. Also, serving it on pretzel buns was probably one of the worst decisions ever made. Your chef needs a major wake up call! Gordon Ramsey needs to come in and inspect this burger nightmare!
Delicious food.  You will not be disappointed.
Delicious food and great service
A favorite location for tasty Family Meals. really nothing but great experiences here, so i will be back. prices were reasonable. food and atmosphere reminds me of kansas city.
A fav place for quality Family Meals. arrived at seven, it wasn't crowded. i look forward to a return visit. kinda of like a place in houston that i enjoyed.
Family Meals and the scene here is above par. I will be back with my coworkers. Bring your hunger - portions are large. Makes me feel like I am back in Sacramento.

The finest tandoori chicken I have ever had in the United States. The staff is super nice and welcoming and respect our likings. Must try if you are in Chicago and like Indian/Pakistani food. if I could this place a 10 I would!!
Highly recommended for spicy food lovers, they have also got some good veggie options. Must try-lamb biriyani
Food is great but what makes this place even better is the staff being so kind and open with their customers. The owners are usually the waiters and they go above and beyond to make you feel welcome
Best food ever! Everything was delicious!
Great place and awesome tandoor 😊😊
Customer service was AMAZING with Faheem as our server, food was great!! Responsibly priced, large portions, authentic food, and BYOB w/cozy seating area. Definitely going back to try other dishes!
Amazing biryani and fresh baked naan. Friendly staff and owners.
Great hospitality. The food is so tasty and the owner is very nice. Definitely recommend!!

Amazing.  Everything on the menu that I ordered was awesome.  Chutney is great.  Meats are great.  Sauces are great.  Naan is Gratz. Mango desert rounds things off nicely.  I smile after I eat here.  😎  Oh and the staff seemed really cool too.  Very attentive when needed.  Cool vibes atmosphere. A must try.  If you live in the neighborhood you’d be ridiculous not to try this place.
Great service, very clean restaurant, good menu, okay food
Love this place one of my favorite great food atmosphere and staff is very nice . Dishes are amazing in here everything taste so fresh
Americanized indian food. It is bland.
Great service ! Great food & awesome atmosphere highly recommended
Great Indian Pakistani food in the middle of the heart of the north side

The food is amazing. However, every time we order from them we are missing something and we call and let the restaurant know they are annoyed or unhelpful. For example, we ordered samosas and don’t get chutney. I’m not sure how we are supposed to eat samosas with out chutney. The customer service is very poor.
GREAT food! Perfectly priced. I couldn’t recommend this place enough. Our waiter was so knowledgeable of the food, attentive, and kind. 10/10 experience.
The host was really friendly, the food was delicious and the portions were more than generous! It is an intimate setting and BYOB! I would highly recommend.
Good food great service just a recommendation need A1 sauce with the steak
The people who run it are gems. What a service and good. Would surely visit again
A preferred scene for delicious family meals. This location is absolutely outstanding. The staff was friendly and sociable. Food is like a place in Baltimore I loved.
A top spot for tasty family meals. I love going here. I will probably become a regular. Bring your hunger - portions are large. Atmosphere is similar to a cafe in San Jose I loved.
Great food and an even better staff

Mouth-watering tandoor delicacies and some creative gems such as the 'Tamarid Chicken Wings' on the menu make this place a must visit in Chicagoland for lovers of Indian/Pakistani cuisine. Service is quick and the amicable servers take great care of the guests. Liked their portions and the dishes seem reasonably priced. Seating is limited so you might wanna make a reservation ahead of time if you are planning to visit during busy hours on the weekend.

I came here last year and I remember it being really good. This time around though it wasn't as good as I recall it. The food wasn't as flavorful and the sauces weren't as tasty. It was still a good meal I just felt like it wasn't as good as it used to be.

This is a phenomenal Indian/Pakistani restaurant.  We ordered the mixed grill, chicken tikka masala, ceviche and assorted breads.  Execution in the kitchen was perfect.  Service was great. The chutneys are out of this world, particularly the carrot ginger one.  The chapathi was perfect.  The restaurant even smells good. I’ve been to dozens of Indian restaurants over the years and this family run place (two brothers from an Indian father and Pakistani mother) definitely stands out.  I was totally impressed.

Best Indian food in Chicago and beyond. The tandoori chicken is to die for. Amazing attentive service with very reasonable prices. Naan is soft fresh and fluffy. Vegetarian options are made fresh and not oily at all. Byob with great street parking. This is the best Indian food I’ve eaten in the US
Had a excellent experience in this spot with my friend. The food arrives quickly and the service is just great. Prices are affordable.

BYOB restaurant with traditional and fusion dishes. Very reasonably priced (about 16-20 for an entree with unlimited rice and chutney). Friendly knowledgeable staff, authentic yet creative dishes. A great place for a relaxing dinner with friends or a date. Would highly recommend.
Great place, great atmosphere, and great food! If you got a taste for Indian food or want to try something new, come here! Just be sure to make a reservation... this place gets busy!!
Family Meals and service at this location is super good. Great food with quality ingredients.  Service is typically above par.

I learned from delivery drivers that the  10% tip I put for a big catering order a few weeks ago did not go to the driver at all. Instead he was given a measly 1c tip which was quite shocking. As I understand it, the owner pocketed the tip on top of charging me quite a bit for the delivery fees. The food was horrible as well. Never am I ordering again from here.
Pricey, more so than most, but the quality is a near match.

Very friendly staff and excellent service. However the meal is mediocre at best. The naan bread was alright, not a lot of spices on the bread just more like just baked bread, although it was made fresh. I got the Chana masala which is vegetarian dish composed of chick peas in a spicy tomato sauce. The chick peas were hard likely undercooked.
Come here all the time, fantastic food and great owner/staff.  Let’s just say we eat here enough the owner knows me by name.  Highly recommend the Lamb Biryani and Karhai
Great food nice guys

Best Indian food we've had in Chicago. We make a point to come here often. It's all delicious and the service is phenomenal as well. It's pretty small inside, so make sure to make a reservation if you don't want to wait.
Delicious food and mango kulfi!!

The best thing was the Masala fries and fresh naan. Chili Chicken Biryani was good.  Tandoori platter, everything was overcooked and dry.. Bhagara baingan was so bad and tasteless - we had to send it back. But they offered to take that off our bill, which is very nice
Super amazing chicken biryani
Authentic with big portions and great service.

Nice authentic Pakistani food at a reasonable price. One of the best I've had in Chicagoland. Just didn't like the fact that they allow people to bring their own alcohol from outside. I wouldn't want to dine with people drinking around me.
Service was good but food was just ok. Lack of flavor, I had the eggplants and were not cooked. Naan bread were good.
Amazing food. Great atmosphere. I recommend a reservation for dinner. It gets busy.
I ordered a chicken Biryani. The rice was not cooked. How can you deliver biryani with uncooked rice. I had to throw all in dust bin.

This food is MUY BUENO. Unique well prepared dishes. The one thing that got me was the unheard of spiciness in this universe. My friends and I thought we were some spicy high rollers and were ballin straight tears in this fine dining environment. We were like camels. Our server practically  became a water boy when we were eating. AND THAT WAS MEDIUM. There's two more LEVELS of hotness: hot and SPICY. Turns out we weren't even in spicy land. Just some weenie hut junior baby sauce land I suppose. You ain't got no taste buds no more if you're eatin spicy. Really fantastic meal tho.
Love love love Tandoor Char House, the owner walked us through the entire meal, explaining the fresh ingredients and spices. Food is phenomenal AND it's BYOB..  a must visit in Chicago, will be back!
Loved it! Reasonably priced, cozy upstairs seating, great food and service
Best Indian food in the city
so delicious every time!

This is my girlfriend and I's favorite Indian Restaurant in Chicago. Their servers are so nice, and they hook you up with their portions. We've only ever had their curries, but their Char Chicken smells incredible every time we go. One of these days, we'll order it!
The food was amazing, and the service was quite possibly the best service I've received in Chicago. The wait staff was friendly and attentive, and the chef was helpful with dietary restrictions.
Awesome place! The owners and staff are friendly and the food is incredible.
Great place for halal steak. Great taste and service. Bit small and packed though but worth waiting for. Reservations highly suggested.
Great food, great taste.

Every time we go we have such great service. The owner will regularly check in and see how things are going. Very attentive and you never have to wait for water. (Huge plus)  The chaat fries are my favorite thing on earth. The seasoning is wonderful and I would like to put that on all food I eat.  I usually go with the chicken tikka masala, always good. But they have so many great items on the menu.  This fusion restaurant is the best of all worlds. Fantastic date place, great for small parties and great just to get delivered or pickup.
They make a sweet buter chicken I never eat before sweet buter chicken
Nice and friendly stuff

Three words: Chicken Tikka Masala!  I like a little spice so the chef graciously made ours a little spicy. Every. Bite. Was. Heavenly 😋  We also got the Rib Eye medium well done with a side of the same sauce as the tikka masala. Again, unbelievably delicious.  Waiters and the owners (one who is the chef) very kind and awesome service. They came to our table several times to make sure everything was okay.  Unique to the restaurant: Mango Cheesecake. 👍
The most friendly staff and terrific food!
If you order a delivery from here and leave tip for driver, they're not giving it to the driver.

This is one of the better Indian restaurants in Chicago. Lots of unique items on the menu. The spicy curly fries provide an inserting twist to traditional fries but can be a bit salty. All tandoori dishes are great. Definately try the biriyani.

Really appreciated the experience.This restaurant is an amazing discovery in Chicago .If you like Indian food or even if you want to try Indian , this  is the place to go. Small and simple, not a trendy restaurant, with a very good menu , lots of choice ,everything we tried was absolutely delicious. It is a type of restaurant that makes a difference. Just wonderful Indian food great lamb ,chicken ,and vegetarian plates. The service is remarkable friendly and just perfect plus this is a BYOB restaurant. The portions are huge. By far , this is one of the best Indian restaurants we tried anywhere. It is also very popular as a take out or orders (the phone almost doesn’t stop ringing)  Thanks! Joe and Francois
Great food and amazing service. Fahim's recommended ribeye steak was really good. 10/10 would recommend!
Quite possibly the best steak I've ever had. Simply Spectacular!
Fahim's recommended T-bone steak was amazing!

The portions were really good, and I do not have anything negative to say about this place, if I consciously tried to be critical. We also tried their masala chai, and that was really good too. Thank you Tandoor Char house for providing me with my most memorable experience in Chicago.

Best Indian food in Chicago, hands down!  Not only is this restaurant amazing to dine at, but wonderful to receive delivery from! Decided to order a little late night Indian Food from Tandoor Char House cause #millennial I’ve been here numerous times before and the food is amazing but I was always suspicious of the quantity that is received for the price. This time I was extremely disappointed by the amount of food that was given. There were only maybe 5 pieces of chicken and 1 little slab of beef in the chicken tikka masala and beef nehari that was ordered!!!  Paying $15+ for only sauce is pretty ridiculous, albeit a delicious sauce, but I’m not ordering ragu for pasta. This time I was let down and had to say something!
The most welcoming restaurant you will go to in Chicago! The hospitality and the food are unmatched. Will come back again and again!

Great food and service. Owner is very attentive. Let him know what your likes are and how spicy, then let him choose your dishes for you. BYOB.

I have been a fan of Tandoor Char House since 2012 when I first discovered them. The Sardharia brothers go above and beyond to ensure their customers are happy and enjoy their meal. So when I was planning my Indian/Muslim wedding recently, I did not hesitate to reach out to Tandoor Char House for their catering services. Faraz, the catering manager, was a pleasure to work with. He was responsive to calls and emails, attentive to detail, and customized a menu that worked for us and our budget. He went above and beyond, offering his staff to serve the wedding cake. The day of the event, he worked tirelessly to ensure the buffet looks great and was always topped up. The food was DELICIOUS - all of our guests commented on the quality of the food, the rich flavors, and how much they enjoyed it. If you are looking for Indian food for your event, I highly highly recommend Tandoor Char House. The service is impeccable and the quality of food surpasses all other Indian food caterers in Chicago (in my humble opinion).

A small place with a big plates and great dishes! The tandoori chicken is amazing and the chutney's that go with it make the dinner satisfying. Not to mention it's BYOB. A little loud in the dining space but that comes with the territory of being small. The family run place really adds to the charm. All in all it's highly recommendable and the prices are very fair, spent about $65 for 2 and had plenty of leftovers.

Amazing food and customer service. My friend and I went here for our first time exploring new options with Indian food. Needless to say this is a new go-to. We both ordered the tandoori chicken wrap on garlic naan which was not only huge in size but amazing in flavor. We ended with their in-house mango cheesecake- to die for! This little hole in the wall had excellent food and generous portions. Wait staff was friendly and attentive. Food was served hot and was tasty. Everything looked fresh. This is uniquely an Indian restaurant with a Pakistani twist. The restaurant is small but cozy and the atmosphere is comfortable and friendly. The food here is definitely authentic and delicious and meets the standards of any critical Indian connoisseur.  The vegetables pakoras are a little different in terms of how they are traditionally prepared but it's good non the less. The tandoori chicken that comes on a sizzling plate is so flavorful and aromatic that you will want to order a second one. The assorted naan basket is a nice way to try the various naan breads such as garlic, cheese, and plain. This place does not short change you on chutneys, including the homemade pickles for condiments. You want more, just ask.  Another plus for this establishment is you can bring your own wine or alcoholic beverages as it is a BYOB. The staff is more than happy to keep to keep your drinks chilled. Speaking of the staff, they are all really friendly, jovial, and professional. We had a good time here and enjoyed every single dish.

Since moving to Chicago a little over a year ago, we have dined at Tandoor Char House more than at any other restaurant in Chicago! We love this family-owned spot with recipes you can tell have been built upon for generations. The Masala sauce is out of this world and the achar is perfect! Our food has always been fresh. Service is unmatched and one of the owners recognized me and my husband since our very first visit offering us free chutney to take home, and he has recognized us ever since! Tandoor Char House should be the prototype for service, freshness, and a perfect blend of intricacy of flavor and simplicity of ingredient. We love it here, we being every friend who visits us, and we hope for their continued success and longevity. Coming here feels like a dream each time.

I absolutely loved this place. Great food, reasonable prices, wonderful service.  One very large problem that has been keeping me from Tandoor is the smell. Since about a year ago, there has been an awful odor in the restaurant. It basically smells like urine; I think there's something wrong with the plumbing and it completely ruins the dining experience.  Tandoor's management really needs to address this issue. It's one of my favorite Indian restaurants but I can't recommend it because of the smell.

My girlfriend and I have been meaning to try this place for over a year. We live in the area, and have walked past dozens of time. Well last night, we finally made a res and had dinner, and we're kicking ourselves for waiting so long to eat here. The food was DELICIOUS. It's a small, almost family style setting, but it's not cramped or stuffy. The owners and founders run around and help take tables and talk about the food, of which they are very passionate, and with good reason. Each item we tried was as tasty as the next, and the the fact they are BYOB adds a bit to the appeal: you can pick up a $15 bottle of wine and enjoy a meal you'd be proud to show any "out-of-towner." HIGHLY recommended, and definitely come with an appetite, or a plan to take a to go box.

Friendly owner and wait staff, delicious pickle (achaar) which is apparently a secret family recipe. The food though, very meh. We ordered the chicken curry and it was very average. Unlikely that I will go back.

OK food - not real Indian but close enough. Very good according to US standards. And really nice.  Small place. No alcohol. Friendly people. Service not really fast.  Making a reservation through OpenTable - a dreadful service - did not work. I just went there.  Papadums were good. Accompanying chutney was interesting but not really a chutney. Salad so-so. Paratha not bad but not very crispy (instead, bit soggy). Rice OK. Fish tikka masala nice, spicy, bit too wet.  All in all a nice dinner which resembled Indian food in a way one would not often find in the US. Reasonably priced.

We used Tandoor for catering a large party at my place of employment, and they exceeded every expectation: the food was delicious and fresh, the service was friendly and professional during all of our correspondences, and it got rave reviews from the faculty and staff.  Kudos to Faraz, Bridget, and Ryan.
